## Project Built

### Banking Application

To apply the concepts I learned, I built a simple Banking Application using C# and Windows Forms.

#### Features Implemented

* Create Bank Accounts
* Support for Current Account and Savings Account
* Deposit Functionality
* Withdrawal Functionality
* Balance Management
* Unique Account Number Generation using Guid
* Display Account Information using DataGridView

#### Concepts Used

* Classes and Objects
* Inheritance
* Collections (List<BankAccount>)
* Event Handling
* Properties
* Constructors
* Data Binding
* Windows Forms Controls

## Challenges Faced

* Understanding event handling in Windows Forms
* Debugging button click events
* Managing DataGridView selections
* Refreshing data after transactions

## Key Takeaways

Building a real project helped me understand how Object-Oriented Programming concepts are used in practical applications. I also learned how to debug issues and connect UI elements with backend logic.

